GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 949
Short Title: Fully Fund School Psychologists & Counselors. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Mohammed, Murdock, and Theodros (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
May 4, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO FULLY FUND SCHOOL PSYCHOLOGIST AND SCHOOL COUNSELOR
3 POSITIONS PER THE LEANDRO COMPREHENSIVE REMEDIAL PLAN.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
6 Public Instruction the sum of three hundred fifty-nine million three hundred thousand dollars
7 ($359,300,000) in recurring funds beginning in the 2026-2027 fiscal year to increase the School
8 Health Personnel Allotment. These funds shall be used to establish a tiered system of support for
9 students by increasing positions for the following school health support personnel in order to
10 meet the following statewide ratios:
11 (1) At least one school psychologist for every 700 students.
12 (2) At least one school counselor for every 250 students.
13 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*S949-v-1*

